of Covarrubias and the Master of the Simpson Carson Madonna -- tCurriculum vitae of Stephen N. Fliegel -- tNotes on Contributors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume celebrates the storied career of Stephen N. Fliegel, the former Robert Bergman Curator of Medieval Art at the Cleveland Museum of Art (CMA). Authors of these essays, all leading curators in their fields, offer insights into curatorial practices by highlighting key objects in some of the most important medieval collections in North America and Europe: Metropolitan Museum of Art, The Louvre, the British Museum, Victoria & Albert Museum, the Getty, the Groeningemuseum, The Morgan Library, Vienna’s Kunsthistorisches Museum, and, of course, the CMA, offering perspectives on the histories of collecting and display, artistic identity, and patronage, with special foci on Burgundian art, acquisition histories, and objects in the CMA.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aKunst/Mittelalter. 4aKunstsammlungen. 4aKuratorische Praxis. 7aART / History / Medieval.2bisacsh  aCollecting.  aCuratorial Practices.  aDisplay.  aMedieval Art.1 aBeer, Lloyd de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorchert, Till-Holger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGertsman, Elina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGertsman, Elina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHindman, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJugie, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrause, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLa Rocca, Donald J., econtributor.